aa(lp246
VI'm going to now just give you some of the data from that first approach.
p247
aVAnd in order to do that
p248
aVI have to explain a little bit about how genes work.
p249
aa(lp250
VSo you probably all know
p251
aVthat genes are made of double-stranded DNA.
p252
aVIt's wound very tightly into chromosomes
p253
aVthat are present in every cell of your body or in a plant's body.
p254
aVIf you unwind that DNA, you get genes.
p255
aVAnd each gene has a promoter,
p256
aVwhich is just an on-off switch,
p257
aVthe gene coding region,
p258
aVand then a terminator,
p259
aVwhich indicates that this is the end of this gene, the next gene will start.
p260
aa(lp261
VNow, promoters are not simple on-off switches.
p262
aVThey normally require a lot of fine-tuning,
p263
aVlots of things to be present and correct before that gene is switched on.
p264
aVSo what's typically done in biotech studies
p265
aVis that we use an inducible promoter,
p266
aVwe know how to switch it on.
p267
aVWe couple that to genes of interest
p268
aVand put that into a plant and see how the plant responds.
p269
aa(lp270
VIn the study that I'm going to talk to you about,
p271
aVmy collaborators used a drought-induced promoter,
p272
aVwhich we discovered in a resurrection plant.
p273
aVThe nice thing about this promoter is that we do nothing.
p274
aVThe plant itself senses drought.
p275
aVAnd we've used it to drive antioxidant genes from resurrection plants.
p276
aVWhy antioxidant genes?
p277
aVWell, all stresses, particularly drought stress,
p278
aVresults in the formation of free radicals,
p279
aVor reactive oxygen species,
p280
aVwhich are highly damaging and can cause crop death.
p281
aVWhat antioxidants do is stop that damage.
p282
aa(lp283
VSo here's some data from a maize strain that's very popularly used in Africa.
p284
aVTo the left of the arrow are plants without the genes,
p285
aVto the right \u2014
p286
aVplants with the antioxidant genes.
p287
aVAfter three weeks without watering,
p288
aVthe ones with the genes do a hell of a lot better.
